					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/homeless-heterotroph" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2241006); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2241006&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183402" alt="Homeless Heterotroph" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2241006)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/homeless-heterotroph" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2241006); return false;" >Homeless Heterotroph</a></span> <span class="odate time_1526855961 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">20 May 2018 22:39</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3806907">
									

<p>I'm onboard with Seagull here, i found the article choppy to say the least. I wasn't particularly intrigued by the dialog either. The Scenario that the article starts out with is killer in concept, but sadly, very very poorly preformed. Normally i'd be moved by such an introduction, but i just wasn't and therefor didn't have it in me to hold the remainder of the article to a impartial regard. Some specifics of why i disliked it.</p>
<ul>
<li>There is nothing more laborious then reading a setting in layman's terms, unless it's intriguingly put into layman's terms. I'm bored to death by reading though the first paragraph of this because i can't visualize any of it. Perhaps if this article started with &quot;I'm your daughter&quot; &quot;Wha-, I have no daughter! I have sons! Two sons!&quot; you could have gotten me interested. But it doesn't it starts with witty or interesting dialogue, it starts with a setting thats boring to read.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>On the subject of the dialogue itself, it seems to be drawn-out and simplified. While that would be fine if it where, say, a dialogue that established characters thought as feelings, its not that, it is a continues dialogue without any kind of hook.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Come one, you can come up with better descriptive text then: &quot;The heartbeat monitor&quot;.</li>
</ul>

							</div>

								
